sitters.name: Marian & Roger
sitters.about: We retired from livestock farming, after having spent more than 50 years in the industry. We are non-smokers, non-drinkers, and have our own transport.

sitters.name: Stacie
sitters.about: Professional: Former psychology, criminal justice, & education adjunct professor for several colleges/universities. Currently work remotely for a media company that produces health research docuseries (e.g., cancer, vaccines, pet health).

sitters.name: Robert
sitters.about: I am a retired Police Officer, with 32 years service in the New South Wales Police Force, I am a Justice of the Peace Volunteering one day a week, a Blood and Plasma Donor, giving up to this date 256 Donations, am a Second Dan Black Belt in Karate, Was nominated and won the District Volunteer of the year award in 2010 due to the many organisations I was involved in volunteering in.

sitters.name: Sharon
sitters.about: Friendly, married female, traveling solo; nonsmoker, non-drinker; who enjoys looking after cats, dogs, and some other small animals; and keeping a tidy home.

sitters.name: Sarah & Alex
sitters.about: We are a couple from the UK in our 40's. We have owned our own home for 16 years and have experience with a wide range of pets. Alex has worked in media and PR for over 15 years, as a Press and PR manager for two UK universities and previously as a journalist on an evening regional paper.
